description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Service Support Manager - CNWL Talking Therapies (IAPT) - Great opportunity&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is an exciting opportunity for an enthusiastic, self-motivated individual who is interested in Strategic planning, Communication, Marketing and delivery of high quality support to CNWL Talking Therapies Clinical network in the boroughs of Westminster, Brent, Harrow, Hillingdon, and Kensington and Chelsea.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for a dynamic individual who has a desire to improve ways of working and systems in a busy and fast paced large IAPT teams.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will support the CNWL talking Therapies Strategic Network team through excellent project management, data analysis, people management and communicating. You will need to work under your own initiative and be able to both lead on projects and work as part of a team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post-holder will be a self-motivated individual who has an organised and logical approach to work and enjoys working flexibly under pressure in a busy team as well as working on your own initiative to achieve deadlines.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post can be challenging and hugely rewarding - you will be supported by your peers, colleagues and managers with regular team meetings, as well as managerial supervision.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for someone with:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to Co-ordinate the delivery of various small to medium-sized projects associated with the implementation and development of the services&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong communication skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to negotiate diplomatically and effectively with staff at all levels&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience of collection of digital analytics to ensure proper evaluation of work and constant Improvement, ongoing optimisation of tracking and implementing changes (through Google Analytics, Google Tag Manager, etc.)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience of managing campaigns on social media&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identifying opportunities to leverage and optimise internal tools and technology to improve business processes&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Interview Date: TBC&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Name Samuel Owiredu&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Job title Service and Performance Manager&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email address Samuel.Owiredu2@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
